Package xxl.core.io.fat.errors

Contains errors for the fat implementation.

See:
          Description

Exception Summary
DirectoryException This class is the top exception of this project.
FileDoesntExist Error class that is be thrown if the specified filename doesn't exist.
IllegalName Error that is thrown in case the name of the file is illegal, that is, if it contains chars that are not allowed.
InitializationException Error which will be thrown if something couldn't be initialized.
InvalidValue Error which will be thrown if something has a wrong value.
NameAllreadyExists Error which will be thrown if there is already a file with this name in the same directory.
NotEnoughMemory Error which will be thrown if there is not enough memory left.
NotFSISector Error which will be thrown if this sector is not a FSI-sector.
WrongFATType Error which will be thrown if an operation is used that is only valid for an other FAT type.
WrongLength Error which will be thrown if something has a wrong length.
 

Package xxl.core.io.fat.errors Description

Contains errors for the fat implementation.
